LAGOS – The National Reconciliation Committee of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) is currently in Ilorin, the Kwara state capital in its bid to unite warring party members in the state. The state is currently divided into camps, one belonging to the state governor, Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq and the other belonging to Alhaji Lai Mohammed, the Minister of Information and Culture. While the national Caretaker Committee of the APC recognised the Abdulrazaq group as the authentic APC, the Lai Mohammed faction has been threatening to work against the APC’s interests in the forthcoming election. Remembrance: Military Men Make Unquantifiable Sacrifices,… School Resumption: Oyo Govt Not Impressed With Low Turnout A member of the reconciliation who spoke with DAILY INDEPENDENT on Monday said they were just on a courtesy visit to the Governor. Details later…